Two other suspected criminals who escaped from the Hlanganani police cells outside Giyani were re-arrested on Saturday. JOHANNESBURG The police in Limpopo say they are following leads which may help them re-arrest five awaiting trial prisoners who escaped from the Musina police holding cells on Friday night.The incident is the fourth recorded in one month in the province.Two suspected criminals who escaped from the Hlanganani police cells outside Giyani last week were re-arrested on Saturdays.Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe says with the help of South Africans, 12 suspects will be brought back into lawful custody. The task team is following all the escapees, and we are still appealing to all members of the community to come forward with information. 